search::displayForm()

Description
    public string search::displayForm([int $rows = 1 [, bool $addGet = TRUE]])
    Generates the appropriate

Parameters
    rows
	Optional.  Unsigned integer.  Specifies the number of fields appearing on a given page.

    addGet
	Optional.  Boolean value.  Specifies whether or not to append a query string to the action attribute of the containing form tag.

Return Values
    Returns a string containing HTML.

Examples
    Example #1
	<?
	print "<h1>Search</h1>";
	print $searchObj->displayForm(3);
	?>

    Example #2
	<?
	print "<h1>Search</h1>";
	print $searchObj->displayForm();
	?>
